<font color="#FF0000">THE WALL</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec  1 18:01:39 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
oh, the wall. I was in D.C. last year and I couldn't go there.<br>
I wanted to so I could honor my bros. who couldn't come home.<br>
But  I couldn't. The rage and pain were too great.<br>
I want the names of us who came home and died to be on that wall.<br>
All of who came back stateside to be spit upon, called <br>
&quot;baby-killers and ostrasized by our peers.<br>
All of us who couldn't handle it and died by our own hand<br>
using drugs,  booze or guns to find peace and acceptance.<br>
Why aren't their names on the wall?<br>
Are they not casualities of that war. Did they not die &quot;in sevice of their
country&quot;?
